      "code": "import sys\nfrom bisect import bisect_right\n\ndef solve():\n    input_data = sys.stdin.buffer.read().split()\n    n = int(input_data[0])\n    a = list(map(int, input_data[1:n+1]))\n    \n    elements = []\n    for i in range(1, n+1):\n        v = a[i-1]\n        if v <= i:\n            d = i - v\n            elements.append((v, -d, d))  # sort by v asc, d desc (use -d for secondary sort)\n    \n    elements.sort(key=lambda x: (x[0], x[1]))\n    \n    # Find longest non-decreasing subsequence of d values\n    # Using patience sorting: maintain tails where tails[i] = smallest ending value of non-decreasing subseq of length i+1\n    tails = []\n    for _, _, d in elements:\n        # Find rightmost position where tails[pos] <= d\n        pos = bisect_right(tails, d)\n        if pos == len(tails):\n            tails.append(d)\n        else:\n            tails[pos] = d\n    \n    print(len(tails))\n\nsolve()",
